Package: firebehavioR
Title: Prediction of Wildland Fire Behavior and Hazard
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Justin", "Ziegler", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "Justin.Ziegler@colostate.edu")
Description: Fire behavior prediction models, including the Rothermel Wildland Fire Modelling System (Scott & Reinhardt 2001; DOI:10.2737/RMRS-RP-29) and Alexander et al.'s (2006) Crown Fire Initiation & Spread model (DOI:10.1016/j.foreco.2006.08.174). Also contains sample datasets, estimation of fire behavior prediction model inputs (e.g., fuel moisture, canopy characteristics, wind adjustment factor), results visualization, and 15 methods to estimate fire weather hazard.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.0)
Imports: ggplot2, utils
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, reshape2, truncnorm, xtable
VignetteBuilder: knitr
